               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra (in full or partly); a few lines, alternating with black lines, on the incipit page of Text I; incipit of Texts II, III, IV, V; the initial line of the note on fols. 41v-42r; a few other words, sälam (and its abbreviations) (e.g., fols. 9r, 19r), sǝbḥat (e.g., fol. 31v), sägid (fol. 39v), tǝnśaʾe (fol. 30v); some letters of the word rǝḫrǝḫtä (fol. 36v); elements of the punctuation signs and the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- In Text II (Mälkǝʾa Iyäsus) the last two strophes, “Sälam sälam lä-kwǝllon...” and “ʾAmlak mǝdr wä-sämayat...” are missing (cp. Mälkǝʾa gubaʾe, ʾAśmära 1974 E.C., p. 48).</note>
                  </msItem>
